        "body": "Would it be useful to add `chunks='auto'` as a default argument to `da.eye()`, then apply the logic that @mrocklin described above?  It seems to me that this is the common behavior for most if not all other functions in `array/creation.py` module. \r\n\r\n```python\r\nIn [9]: with dask.config.set({'array.chunk-size': '50 MiB'}): \r\n   ...:     x = da.eye(500000, 'auto') \r\n   ...:     print(x) \r\n   ...:                                                                              \r\ndask.array<eye, shape=(500000, 500000), dtype=float64, chunksize=(2500, 2500)>\r\n```",
